==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hockey
<hw>Hock"ey</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From <er>Hook</er>,
<pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A game in which two parties of
players, armed with sticks curved or hooked at the end, attempt to drive
any small object (as a ball or a bit of wood) toward opposite
goals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The stick used by the players.</def> <altsp>[Written
also <asp>hookey</asp> and <asp>hawkey</asp>.]</altsp> <-- ice hockey,
hockey puck -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hockherb</ent>⟦br⟧
